## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-102">Usare un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> azione con un <xref:System.Windows.EventTrigger> oppure <xref:System.Windows.Trigger> arrestare in modo interattivo un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-102">Use a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> action with an <xref:System.Windows.EventTrigger> or <xref:System.Windows.Trigger> to interactively stop a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> influisce solo su un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> quando è attiva (dopo il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> inizia).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard> only affects a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> when it is active (after the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> starts).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-104">L'arresto di uno storyboard il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentGlobalSpeedInvalidated> e <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentStateInvalidated> eventi, ma non la <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Completed> evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-104">Stopping a storyboard triggers the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentGlobalSpeedInvalidated> and <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.CurrentStateInvalidated> events, but not the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Timeline.Completed> event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-105"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> non fa riferimento a un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> direttamente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-105"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> does not reference a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> directly.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-106">Piuttosto <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> deve fare riferimento il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> del <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> che controlla il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-106">Rather, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> must reference the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> that controls the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-107">Visualizzare [procedura: usare i trigger di evento per controllare un Storyboard dopo il relativo avvio](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) per un esempio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-107">See [How to: Use Event Triggers to Control a Storyboard After It Starts](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) for an example.</span></span>  
  
## <a name="pause-resume-stop-or-otherwise-control-a-storyboard-interactively"></a><span data-ttu-id="af5b4-108">Sospendere, riprendere, arrestare o in caso contrario controllare uno Storyboard in modo interattivo</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-108">Pause, Resume, Stop, or Otherwise Control a Storyboard Interactively</span></span>  
 <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-109">Per poter sospendere, riprendere o altrimenti controllare un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Storyboard%2A> in modo interattivo, impostare il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> proprietà del relativo <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> e usare un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ControllableStoryboardAction> oggetto (, ad esempio <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ResumeStoryboard>, o <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard>) controllarla da riferimento relativo <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-109">To be able to pause, resume, or otherwise control a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Storyboard%2A> interactively, set the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> property of its <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> and use a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ControllableStoryboardAction> object (such as <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ResumeStoryboard>, or <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.StopStoryboard>) to control it by referencing its <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-110">Se il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> dei <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> non è specificato, il <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Storyboard%2A> non è possibile controllare in modo interattivo dopo l'inizio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-110">If the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> is unspecified, the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Storyboard%2A> cannot be interactively controlled after it is begun.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="af5b4-111">Visualizzare [procedura: usare i trigger di evento per controllare un Storyboard dopo il relativo avvio](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) per altre informazioni.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="af5b4-111">See [How to: Use Event Triggers to Control a Storyboard After It Starts](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) for more information.</span></span>  
  
